After looking at some scripts the second parameter seems to be an id of some kind. Here are some I f
ound from some R* scripts:  

"miss_Tower_01" (this went from 01 - 10)  

"miss_Ass0" (0, 4, 6, 3)  

"MISS_PATROL_8"  

I think they're patrol routes, but I'm not sure. And I believe the 3rd parameter is a BOOL, but I ca
n't confirm other than only seeing 0 and 1 being passed.  

As far as I can see the patrol routes names such as "miss_Ass0" have been defined earlier in the scr
ipts. This leads me to believe we can defined our own new patrol routes by following the same approa
ch.   

