CLOCK::GET_POSIX_TIME(int* year, int* month, int* day, int* hour, int* minute, int* second);
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
```

Gets system time as year, month, day, hour, minute and second.  

Example usage:  

	int year;  

	int month;  

	int day;  

	int hour;  

	int minute;  

	int second;  

	TIME::GET_POSIX_TIME(&year, &month, &day, &hour, &minute, &second);  

